The surface morphology, structure, and consistence of TNA and TNA-GO samples were investigated using SEM, TEM and EDX (Fig. 1
                        ). From Fig. 2
                        a, which shows the SEM image of TNA from top view, highly ordered TNA grown on a Ti substrate were observed. The nanotubes formed in TNA were uniformly distributed and similar in size, with approximate wide tube diameter of 120nm. The surface of TNA was relatively smooth. Meanwhile, the SEM images of TNA from side view were shown in Fig. 2c and d. From the side-view images the length of nanotubes in TNA can determined as about 20μm (medium tubes [9]). More detailed information regarding structural features were displayed in TEM images of TNA (Fig. 2e and f). TEM images further confirmed that the diameter of the nanotubes in TNA was about 120nm with wall thickness of about 20nm.
